Dozens of grant beneficiaries slept outside a Sassa office in Gugulethu last night to ensure they were near the front of the line when it opened. eNCA's Monique Mortlock is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Dozens of grant beneficiaries slept outside a Sassa office in Gugulethu on Tuesday night to ensure they were near the front of the queue when it opened. As part of adhering to COVID-19 protocols, the branch allows only a limited number of people inside. Similar queues were also seen at the Sassa office in Eerste River. READ: Sassa suspends more than 200,000 temporary disability grants Sassa's Regional Executive Manager, Bandile Maqetuka, says a booking system has been implemented for grant beneficiaries. This in an effort to make operations smooth.